<div class="FunctionDoc YAMLDoc" id="text_input-__init__" markdown="1">

## [function __text\_input\.\_\_init\_\___\(form, center=False, text=u'', frame=True, stub=u'Type here \.\.\.', return\_accepts=False, var=None\)](#function-__text_input__init____form-centerfalse-textu-frametrue-stubutype-here-return_acceptsfalse-varnone) {#function-__text_input__init____form-centerfalse-textu-frametrue-stubutype-here-return_acceptsfalse-varnone}

Constructor.

__Arguments:__

- `form` -- The parent form.
	- Type: form

__Keywords:__

- `stub` -- A text string that should be shown whenever the user has not entered any text.
	- Default: u'Type here ...'
	- Type: str, unicode
- `return_accepts` -- Indicates whether a return press should accept and close the form.
	- Default: False
	- Type: bool
- `center` -- Indicates whether the text should be centered.
	- Default: False
	- Type: bool
- `var` -- The name of the experimental variable that should be used to log the widget status.
	- Default: None
	- Type: str, unicode, NoneType
- `text` -- The text to start with.
	- Default: u''
	- Type: str, unicode
- `frame` -- Indicates whether a frame should be drawn around the widget.
	- Default: True
	- Type: bool

</div>

